title: University of Georgia 4/29 Protests (University of Georgia)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I respectfully request email communications between UGA PD, Jere Morehead, S. Jack Hu,
Michelle G. Cook, Rebecca Scarboro, Brett Malone, and P. Daniel Silk and the Georgia Governor's office, any communications referencing any discussions with the Office of the Georgia Governor between UGA PD and the above parties (or any representative thereof), and any communications between the above parties amongst themselves (or any representatives thereof), from April 1, 2024 until current date (5/2/24). This search is to include anyone operating in capacity as representative
from the office of the above individuals, and include anyone operating in capacity as
representative from the Governor's office (anyone with an email address ending in
@georgia.gov). Search terms are to include "Protest," "Columbia," "Palestine," "Gaza," "Israel,"
"Hamas," "Agitators."

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Josh Lingsch

title: Edin Alex Enamorado "The Justice 8" (San Bernardino County Sheriff)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any correspondence between the San Bernardino Sheriff department and/or Fontana city Mayor Acquanetta Warren and/or San Bernardino district attorney and/or Pamona Police department regarding Edin Alex Enamorado and or anyone involved what is known as the "Justice 8".

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

sennett
